Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.20,0:00:02.77,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}My name's Conan Edogawa!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.77,0:00:05.70,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}High school student Shin'ichi was\Nforced to take a drug that shrunk him!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.70,0:00:08.70,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Although smaller, my mind remains\Nthat of a sharp detective!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.70,0:00:11.97,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Today's case is on location for a TV drama!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.97,0:00:15.43,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}No matter how good an actor is,\Nthere is always only one truth!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.52,0:01:55.96,Dialogue Top,,0000,0000,0000,,"Beika Shrine"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.43,0:02:15.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.70,0:02:20.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I never meant to kill you!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.89,0:02:23.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.70,0:02:26.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Cut!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.31,0:02:28.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,OK! That's it for this scene!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.58,0:02:31.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That was some fine acting, Yoko!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.98,0:02:34.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Filming a TV drama is interesting,\Ndon't you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.45,0:02:35.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.78,0:02:38.28,Character Card,,0000,0000,0000,,Popular Idol\NYoko Okino (21)
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.82,0:02:38.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.99,0:02:45.20,Character Card,,0000,0000,0000,,Leading Man\NShingo Nachi (23)
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.79,0:02:45.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,As if the great leading man\NNachi Shingo would ever mess up!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.20,0:02:48.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yoko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}! You must be exhausted!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.33,0:02:50.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.10,0:02:52.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What an amazing performance that was!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.90,0:02:54.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm absolutely certain that this drama
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.71,0:02:56.42,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Tuesday Suspense Drama
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.71,0:02:56.42,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,"The Blackmailers Who Scoff\Nin the Darkness"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.71,0:02:56.42,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Shooting Script
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.71,0:02:56.42,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Nichiuri TV
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.53,0:02:56.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,will go down as a masterpiece!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.57,0:03:01.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But only because you helped\Nsupervise the mystery writing!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.07,0:03:02.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.58,0:03:04.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We have with us the famous\Ndetective who's known
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.74,0:03:06.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,as the modern-day Kogoro Akechi!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.10,0:03:09.06,Character Card,,0000,0000,0000,,Director\NTaketoshi Gondo (57)
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.10,0:03:09.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This drama's going to be a\Nsmash hit, no doubt about it!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.06,0:03:12.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I suppose I did help a lot!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.36,0:03:18.42,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}He's on top of the world now...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.42,0:03:22.76,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}This goes here, and this goes like this...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.76,0:03:24.50,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Way too easy...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.50,0:03:26.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, you!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.27,0:03:28.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be touching my things!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.37,0:03:30.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, Nachi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.24,0:03:33.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I wasn't paying close enough attention to him...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.71,0:03:37.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I guess I can forgive him\Nif it's for a cute girl like you...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.18,0:03:39.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.01,0:03:41.35,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Bah. What a smooth talker.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.35,0:03:45.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You're into matchstick puzzles, Nachi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.39,0:03:50.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, leading men like me\Nprefer intelligent hobbies.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.72,0:03:54.27,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Oh, is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.27,0:03:57.86,Character Card,,0000,0000,0000,,Continuity Checker\NTaeko Mamegaki (24)
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.43,0:03:56.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Nachi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}! Good work today!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.86,0:03:58.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Here's a towel!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.08,0:04:00.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.73,0:04:04.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, would you have dinner with me tonight?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.07,0:04:05.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, I can't!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.16,0:04:06.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.64,0:04:08.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.78,0:04:11.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She and this kid are getting hitched next month.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.68,0:04:12.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ain't that right, Shimazaki?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.87,0:04:16.63,Character Card,,0000,0000,0000,,Assistant Director\NYuji Shimazaki (26)
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.05,0:04:16.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.88,0:04:20.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Really?! Congratulations!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.82,0:04:21.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.89,0:04:25.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,They only seem like flowers\Nbefore you marry them.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.80,0:04:28.43,Character Card,,0000,0000,0000,,Assistant Photographer\NMorio Anzai (25)
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.80,0:04:27.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't know it's an illusion
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.53,0:04:28.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,until it's too late.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.43,0:04:31.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.16,0:04:32.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No, Yuji{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.43,0:04:35.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He always has something bad to say!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.34,0:04:40.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's just what people say.\NI'm not necessarily talking about you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.14,0:04:42.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't get so upset.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.45,0:04:47.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's my watch's alarm.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.25,0:04:52.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Cool sound, huh? I bought it last month\Nwhen I went to America.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.99,0:04:56.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Guess you don't care.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.56,0:04:59.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,See you chumps later.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.06,0:05:01.22,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}What a jerk...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.13,0:05:05.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,One, two, three...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.20,0:05:07.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Are they finished filming?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.53,0:05:08.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, Grandfather.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.80,0:05:11.93,Character Card,,0000,0000,0000,,Taeko's Grandfather\NKyusaku Mamegaki (75)
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.40,0:05:12.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Make sure to clean everything up\Nbefore you leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.34,0:05:15.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Especially things like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.44,0:05:18.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We will, Grandfather!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.08,0:05:20.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I leave it in your hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.81,0:05:24.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Your grandfather is the shrine keeper here?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.65,0:05:27.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, this shrine is where I grew up.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.95,0:05:29.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-neechan{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.56,0:05:33.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't your friend ask you\Nto get Shingo Nachi's autograph?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.56,0:05:34.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I forgot!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.76,0:05:35.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Where is he?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.74,0:05:37.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Already went to change clothes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.60,0:05:38.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh no!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.79,0:05:40.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait a sec, Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-neechan{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.43,0:05:43.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Cut the crap!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.84,0:05:45.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's Nachi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s voice...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.51,0:05:47.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you even have any proof?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.24,0:05:49.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.24,0:05:53.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If you want these photos and negatives,\Nyou know what to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.38,0:05:55.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Money?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.05,0:05:59.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.29,0:06:01.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No, nothing at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.66,0:06:10.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}. We'll be staying at this inn tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.26,0:06:12.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,How about a nice bath and a drink?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.80,0:06:14.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sounds good to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.37,0:06:16.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Give me a break, Dad...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.54,0:06:19.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} should come too!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.41,0:06:20.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sure!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.21,0:06:22.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What a crappy-looking inn!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.58,0:06:26.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A leading man such as me would\Nnever stay in a place like this!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.28,0:06:29.95,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}This constant talk about being a\Nleading man is really annoying...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.95,0:06:33.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be staying at the Teitan Hotel.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.55,0:06:36.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, Nachi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.12,0:06:38.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He's hopeless...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.79,0:06:45.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Drink up, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.10,0:06:47.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry for the wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.17,0:06:49.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Anzai! Where you goin'?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.30,0:06:52.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The camera doesn't keep\Nitself tuned up, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.54,0:06:55.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What an unfriendly fellow.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.44,0:06:59.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuji{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}. I need to take care\Nof something at home...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.18,0:07:03.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay. Hurry back.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.19,0:07:12.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't need make-up,\NRan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}! You're still young!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.33,0:07:14.05,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}That's Shimazaki{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10}!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.06,0:07:18.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Shimazaki! Get me some\Ncigarettes while you're out.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.40,0:07:20.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sure thing!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.87,0:07:24.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}! Let's go to the convenience store!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.54,0:07:28.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But isn't it a bad idea for an idol\Nto walk outside at night?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.41,0:07:30.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be fine!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.08,0:07:34.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Nobody'll recognize me if I change\Nmy hairstyle and wear a hat!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.75,0:07:36.98,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}I saw them changing!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.98,0:07:39.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yoko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}. Are you really sure this is okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.79,0:07:41.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.43,0:07:48.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like Anzai{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s going out too...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.96,0:07:53.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You worry too much, Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.87,0:07:55.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.30,0:07:57.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Taeko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.64,0:08:00.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Taeko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.11,0:08:01.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Taeko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.21,0:08:02.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.71,0:08:04.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Is something the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.85,0:08:06.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.25,0:08:11.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder what that was about...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.85,0:08:14.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She looked like she had seen a ghost...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.76,0:08:18.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.46,0:08:22.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,See? I told you we'd be fine!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.63,0:08:25.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You were right! They didn't recognize you at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.10,0:08:29.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Who was that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.47,0:08:31.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell me it was an offering thief!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.74,0:08:40.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There's someone on the ground!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.88,0:08:44.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Anzai{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.09,0:08:49.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He's dead! Call the police!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.19,0:08:50.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.16,0:08:51.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.73,0:08:59.77,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Even if the victim's hat fell off when he collapsed,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.77,0:09:01.60,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}how did his vest come off?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.87,0:09:09.04,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}This is the knife they used during filming!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.04,0:09:13.77,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Which means that the killer was\Nsomeone on the filming crew!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.09,0:09:22.46,Dialogue Top,,0000,0000,0000,,"Fu Dog"
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.46,0:09:26.63,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}This is a dying message the victim left behind!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.63,0:09:28.19,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}"Fu Dog?"
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.19,0:09:31.19,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Is this a clue to who did it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.87,0:09:39.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You saw someone suspicious\Nbefore you found the body, correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.77,0:09:44.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. But it was too dark to even tell\Nif it was a man or a woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.68,0:09:46.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And that was around 10:30.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.58,0:09:49.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That means the murder\Ntook place between 10:00,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.68,0:09:53.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,when the victim left the inn at 10:30.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.62,0:09:57.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector. This case is surprisingly simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.72,0:09:58.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,How's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.93,0:10:05.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,First off, the murder weapon\Nwas used during the show's filming.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.06,0:10:08.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Second, "Fu Dog" clearly\Nrefers to the Shinto shrine.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.03,0:10:11.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,From these two facts alone...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.17,0:10:13.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,...the killer must be you, Taeko Mamegaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.84,0:10:16.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Nonsense! Taeko would never kill anyone!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.61,0:10:21.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Taeko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}. You were gone for nearly\Nan hour during the party, correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.85,0:10:24.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I needed to get something at home...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.88,0:10:26.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Our house is behind the shrine.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.82,0:10:29.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Can anyone verify that you were there?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.39,0:10:32.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Grandfather was out at the time,\Nso I was the only one there...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.89,0:10:38.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But Taeko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} came back\Njust as Anzai{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} left the inn!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.60,0:10:40.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.40,0:10:44.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,After she came back, she stayed\Nin the hall the whole time...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.47,0:10:48.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That means she couldn't possibly have killed him.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.01,0:10:50.14,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Get a hold of yourself, will ya?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.14,0:10:52.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Any fingerprints on the murder weapon?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.85,0:10:55.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No. But it looks like someone wiped them away.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.62,0:10:56.78,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}That's weird!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.78,0:10:58.82,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}If the killer had time to wipe the fingerprints off,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.82,0:11:01.42,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}why not run off with\Nthe murder weapon instead?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.42,0:11:07.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Did anyone among you leave the inn\Nbetween 10:00 and 10:30?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.03,0:11:12.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Um... I went to buy cigarettes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.16,0:11:14.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,When was this?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.07,0:11:14.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Let me think...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.92,0:11:17.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,9:45!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.50,0:11:19.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I happened to look at my watch just then!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.84,0:11:21.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And when did you return?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.87,0:11:23.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,About 30 minutes later.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.78,0:11:26.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Which would be 10:15?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.29,0:11:27.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.38,0:11:29.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Tell me, Nachi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.08,0:11:31.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I hear you were the only one who\Ndecided to stay at the Teitan Hotel
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.72,0:11:33.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,instead of this inn.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.29,0:11:39.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,My pride as a leading man wouldn't\Nlet me stay in such a hovel!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.06,0:11:42.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Where were you between 10:00 and 10:30?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.76,0:11:45.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I was in the hotel bar until 10:00.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.53,0:11:47.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Plenty of people can vouch for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.19,0:11:49.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm asking about after that!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.54,0:11:51.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I was in my hotel room.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.32,0:11:52.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Can anyone verify this?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.74,0:11:55.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I was by myself, so no!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.74,0:11:59.08,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}The killer's someone on the filming crew...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.08,0:12:03.75,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Our only clue is the phrase "Fu Dog",\Nwhich the victim wrote...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.75,0:12:06.79,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Taeko{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10} is the one most\Nclosely connected to fu dogs...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.79,0:12:12.16,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}But she returned to the inn just\Nas the victim was leaving it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.16,0:12:14.13,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Come to think of it...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.13,0:12:19.03,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}...why was she so surprised then?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.03,0:12:22.03,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Shimazaki{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10} went to buy cigarettes at 9:45
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.03,0:12:24.24,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}and returned to the inn at 10:15.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.24,0:12:26.84,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}More than enough time to commit the murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.84,0:12:30.48,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}But it was 10:30 when we\Nsaw the person at the shrine.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.48,0:12:33.81,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Shimazaki{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10} was back at the inn by then.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.81,0:12:37.78,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Nachi{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10} has no alibi after 10:00—\Nhe could have done it as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.78,0:12:39.92,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}It sounded like he was being\Nblackmailed by the victim,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.92,0:12:42.82,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}so in terms of motive, he's the most suspicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.82,0:12:46.49,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}And Nachi{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10} was most likely\Nthe one we saw in the shadows!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.53,0:12:50.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector! We found these in the victim's room!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.17,0:12:58.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Nachi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}... This is you\Nleaving a hotel with a woman...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.24,0:13:02.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's the actress Ritsuko Hagiyama!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.01,0:13:04.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But she's married!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.91,0:13:07.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Photographic evidence of your infidelity...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.35,0:13:09.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Now that you mention it!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.15,0:13:11.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know something, Ran?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.55,0:13:16.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I saw Anzai{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} trying to\Nblackmail Nachi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} earlier!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.42,0:13:18.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Blackmail?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.69,0:13:20.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So you are the killer!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.93,0:13:22.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I already told you, I didn't do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.76,0:13:26.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If I killed him, then what the\Nhell does "Fu Dog" mean?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.13,0:13:28.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You sure that's not one of your nicknames?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.37,0:13:29.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.84,0:13:36.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No leading man like me, Shingo Nachi,\Nwould have a crappy nickname like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.11,0:13:39.37,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}What exactly does this "Fu Dog" mean?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.25,0:13:43.32,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Wait a second!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.32,0:13:45.72,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Why would he go through the\Ntrouble of writing it down?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.72,0:13:47.79,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}He was killed right in front of a fu dog—
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.79,0:13:50.06,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}all he had to do was point at it!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.06,0:13:53.09,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}There was no need to write it out!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.09,0:13:54.72,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}What's this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.90,0:14:02.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you even have any proof that I was here?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.34,0:14:04.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? This writing is weird!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.40,0:14:06.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This character isn't drawn right!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.47,0:14:08.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That lousy kid's at it again!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.81,0:14:10.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,How many times do I have to—
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.74,0:14:14.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This man was an adult, but he\Ncouldn't even write katakana right!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.81,0:14:16.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What did he draw wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.72,0:14:21.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You're supposed to write this part here all in one stroke.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.49,0:14:24.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But he wrote it using two.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.16,0:14:27.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What now?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.26,0:14:29.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You're right...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.53,0:14:32.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He did the same with the last character too!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.17,0:14:34.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.33,0:14:40.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What if these incorrect strokes were\Nactually lines that were added later?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.31,0:14:42.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"Leading man"?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.84,0:14:46.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The only leading man\Naround here is Shingo Nachi!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.51,0:14:49.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like some definitive\Nproof has shown itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.15,0:14:51.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No! It wasn't me!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.68,0:14:55.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll admit that I was supposed\Nto meet Anzai here at 10:30,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.72,0:14:59.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but when I showed up, he was already dead!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.46,0:15:01.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Enough of this tomfoolery!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.06,0:15:04.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the truth! He really was dead when I got here!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.33,0:15:07.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I was about to run away, but then\NI saw "leading man" written there...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.90,0:15:11.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So I added some vertical lines like\Nin the matchstick puzzles that I do!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.84,0:15:16.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If you're not the killer, then why\Ndid the victim write "leading man"?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.88,0:15:18.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hell if I know!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.71,0:15:19.71,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Wait a minute!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.71,0:15:22.18,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}It's not normal for someone\Nto fake a dying message
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.18,0:15:24.88,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}but not come up with a fake alibi!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.88,0:15:29.62,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Maybe the real killer altered the\Nmessage to say "leading man"!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.36,0:15:37.16,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Could this be what I think it is?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.16,0:15:41.10,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}It {\i1}couldn't{\i0} have been that person!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.37,0:15:46.54,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}What's that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.54,0:15:49.31,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}There's no blood on this watch!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.31,0:15:52.11,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Aha! That's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.11,0:15:54.98,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Now I know the truth behind this case!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.98,0:15:57.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It wasn't me! I didn't do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.45,0:16:01.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Listen to how pathetic you sound,\NMr. Leading Man!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.93,0:16:09.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You can give us the details down at the station.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.70,0:16:12.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Not so fast!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.23,0:16:15.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector Megure. Nachi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} is not the murderer.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.94,0:16:17.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Come again?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.40,0:16:21.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The reason being that the\Nmurder took place before 10:00!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.67,0:16:23.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's impossible!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.51,0:16:25.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about, Dad?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.18,0:16:28.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We saw Anzai{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} leave the inn around 10:00!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.81,0:16:31.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We even heard his watch alarm go off!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.48,0:16:34.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector. Have a look at the victim's wristwatch.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.82,0:16:36.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,His watch?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.29,0:16:40.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,His entire left arm is covered in blood,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.96,0:16:43.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but there's none at all on his watch.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.53,0:16:45.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You're right!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.23,0:16:50.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, someone\Nremoved the watch from the body
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.77,0:16:52.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,after the victim was killed!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.81,0:16:55.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Someone removed his watch?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.11,0:16:57.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This particular person wanted to\Nmake it look like the murder happened
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.98,0:16:59.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,later than it actually did.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.91,0:17:03.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So the killer came up with the idea\Nof taking the watch back to the inn
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.85,0:17:06.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and setting the alarm off in the victim's room.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.35,0:17:09.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But it would cause problems if\Nblood dripped off it on the way back,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.79,0:17:12.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,so the killer wiped the watch clean.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.53,0:17:15.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That means the person we saw at the inn was—
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.56,0:17:18.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right. That wasn't Anzai{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.26,0:17:22.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The person who set the\Nalarm off in Anzai{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s room
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.00,0:17:28.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,put his vest and hat on and left the\Ninn disguised as Anzai{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.04,0:17:31.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This person rushed back to the shrine,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.54,0:17:34.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,put the watch back on the dead body,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.25,0:17:37.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and then dropped the hat and vest nearby!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.15,0:17:42.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then the killer wrote "leading man"\Nto make Nachi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} look guilty!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.36,0:17:44.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If the killer wanted Nachi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} to look guilty,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.29,0:17:46.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,why not just write "Nachi"?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.33,0:17:49.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That would have been a much\Nmore effective way of fooling us!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.43,0:17:51.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The killer couldn't write "Nachi".
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.50,0:17:55.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The reason being that the victim\Nhad already written something
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.13,0:17:56.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,that identified the murderer.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.64,0:17:58.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Something that identified the murderer?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.10,0:17:59.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.44,0:18:02.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"Leading man" was actually a\Nsingle word that the victim wrote,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.11,0:18:05.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,with extra strokes added in later.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.01,0:18:08.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then what was the original\Nword the victim wrote?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.55,0:18:12.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It was "Mame".
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.69,0:18:16.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Taeko Mamegaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}. You're the murderer.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.59,0:18:19.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Nonsense! She would never!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.33,0:18:20.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It couldn't be!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.79,0:18:22.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.26,0:18:28.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Taeko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} returned to the inn just as\Nthe person disguised as Anzai{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} left!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.53,0:18:31.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It was me! I killed Anzai{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.47,0:18:33.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I was the one who dressed up as him!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.87,0:18:35.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But the word "Mame" wasn't written there!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.61,0:18:39.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Shimazaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}. You were indeed\Nthe one who dressed up as him,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.91,0:18:41.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but you cannot possibly be the killer.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.61,0:18:45.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,See the huge spray of blood around the body?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.69,0:18:48.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The killer must have been\Ncovered in a lot of blood as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.52,0:18:52.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But there's not even a single drop on your clothes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.22,0:18:57.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The only person who had time to\Nchange clothes and wash off the blood
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.10,0:18:59.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,was Taeko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.30,0:19:02.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No! I killed him!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.17,0:19:04.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuji{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}. It's over.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.57,0:19:06.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Taeko!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.14,0:19:08.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's just as you said, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.34,0:19:10.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I killed Anzai{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.71,0:19:11.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Taeko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.88,0:19:13.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.11,0:19:18.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I take it you didn't know\NShimazaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} had dressed up as him?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.45,0:19:19.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.59,0:19:25.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So I was really shocked when\NI saw Anzai{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} at the front door...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.26,0:19:28.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I had no idea what was going on anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.03,0:19:31.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But why, Taeko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.36,0:19:36.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Taeko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}. Anzai was\Nblackmailing you too, wasn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.87,0:19:38.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.14,0:19:41.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,When I was in high school,\NI turned rebellious for a short time
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.81,0:19:44.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,after my parents died in an accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.68,0:19:48.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I stopped going to school and started\Nhanging out with the wrong crowd...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.48,0:19:51.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Anzai was one of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.99,0:19:54.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Grandfather.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.52,0:19:58.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Remember when everyone was in an uproar
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.19,0:20:00.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,after that expensive statue was\Nstolen from the shrine storehouse?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.23,0:20:01.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.83,0:20:04.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That was my fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.86,0:20:10.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,After I mentioned it to Anzai,\Nhe immediately went and stole it...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.30,0:20:11.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.87,0:20:14.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Why didn't you tell me?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.01,0:20:15.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I tried to!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.84,0:20:19.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But Sugiyama{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who was\Nin charge of the storehouse,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.51,0:20:22.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,felt responsible for it and killed himself!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.31,0:20:27.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I was too scared to say anything after seeing that!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.45,0:20:30.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,After that, I quit hanging\Naround Anzai and the others,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.22,0:20:32.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and I started taking school seriously again.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.86,0:20:37.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I had nearly managed to suppress\Nthe memories of that detestable event!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.46,0:20:42.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,All I wanted was to marry\NYuji{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and start a happy family!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.33,0:20:44.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But then he showed up!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.54,0:20:47.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And then he tried to blackmail you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.27,0:20:48.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.31,0:20:50.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He said that since I had been an accomplice,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.88,0:20:54.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I was just as responsible\Nfor Sugiyama{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s suicide!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.31,0:20:56.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He told me over and over!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.08,0:21:01.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I felt that if something wasn't done,\Nhe would ruin our marriage!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.32,0:21:07.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I was supposed to pay Anzai\Nsome money here at 9:30 tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.49,0:21:11.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But instead, I brought a knife\Nand threatened Anzai back!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.76,0:21:15.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I told him never to show\Nhis face around me ever again!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.27,0:21:18.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He got mad and rushed for me...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.64,0:21:20.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,...and then the knife just happened to—
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.01,0:21:29.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I never meant to kill him!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.79,0:21:39.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You seemed strange when you left,\Nso I pretended to go buy cigarettes.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.49,0:21:41.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,When I got to the shrine, Anzai was dead,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.13,0:21:44.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and the word "Mame" was written in blood next to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.13,0:21:46.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I figured you were the one who killed him,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.80,0:21:49.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,so I tried my hardest to alter all the evidence!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.34,0:21:50.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I wiped the fingerprints off the knife,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.74,0:21:53.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and took Anzai's watch back to the inn!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.91,0:21:56.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The rest is exactly as Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} deduced.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.34,0:21:59.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I should've just gotten rid of that writing in blood!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.35,0:22:03.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But then I remembered how he\Nthreatened Nachi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} earlier this evening,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.58,0:22:07.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,so I made "Mame" say "leading man" instead!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.42,0:22:10.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm so sorry, Yuji{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}! Forgive me!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.26,0:22:12.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Taeko!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.79,0:24:08.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This door was locked!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.59,0:24:10.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He may have killed himself!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.69,0:24:13.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Nope. This was a murder!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.06,0:24:15.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You're in the way again?!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.30,0:24:18.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Look closely at the doorway!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.93,0:24:22.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The murderer is among the seven of you!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.09,0:24:30.13,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Next Conan:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.13,0:24:35.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Next Conan's Hint: A piece of bread
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.49,0:24:37.21,Dialogue Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Finally, next time is a two-parter!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.21,0:24:39.59,Dialogue Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Will you know the culprit from just the first part?
